'''Onsen-ji''' (温泉寺) is the name of various {{ill|Buddhist temples|ja|仏教寺院|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Buddhist temples|qq=}} across Japan.

* {{ill|Onsen-ji (Nikkō)|ja|温泉寺 (日光市)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen-ji (Nikkō)|qq=}}  -  A [[:en:Tiantai|Tendai sect]] temple in {{ill|Nikkō, Tochigi|ja|日光市, 栃木県|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nikkō, Tochigi|qq=}}, a sub-temple of [[:en:Rinnō-ji|Rinnō-ji]], located in {{ill|Nikkō Yumoto Onsen|ja|日光湯元温泉|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nikkō Yumoto Onsen|qq=}}.
* [[:en:Onsen-ji (Nagano)|Onsen-ji (Suwa)]]  -  A {{ill|Myōshin-ji school of Rinzai Zen|ja|臨済宗妙心寺派|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Myōshin-ji school of Rinzai Zen|qq=}} temple in {{ill|Suwa, Nagano|ja|諏訪市, 長野県|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suwa, Nagano|qq=}}.
* {{ill|Reihōzan Yakuō-in Onsen-ji|ja|温泉寺 (加賀市)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Reihōzan Yakuō-in Onsen-ji|qq=}}  -  A [[:en:Shingon-shū Chisan-ha|Shingon-shū Chisan-ha]] temple in {{ill|Kaga, Ishikawa|ja|加賀市, 石川県|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kaga, Ishikawa|qq=}}, one of the "Five Temples of Hakusan" and the only one still in existence.
* {{ill|Onsen-ji (Atami)|ja|温泉寺 (熱海市)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen-ji (Atami)|qq=}}  -  A Myōshin-ji school of Rinzai Zen temple in {{ill|Atami, Shizuoka|ja|熱海市, 静岡県|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Atami, Shizuoka|qq=}}.
* {{ill|Onsen-ji (Gero)|ja|温泉寺 (下呂市)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen-ji (Gero)|qq=}}  -  A Myōshin-ji school of Rinzai Zen temple in {{ill|Gero, Gifu|ja|下呂市, 岐阜県|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gero, Gifu|qq=}}.
* {{ill|Onsen-ji (Kobe)|ja|温泉寺 (神戸市)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen-ji (Kobe)|qq=}}  -  A [[:en:Ōbaku|Ōbaku sect]] temple in {{ill|Kobe, Hyōgo|ja|神戸市, 兵庫県|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kobe, Hyōgo|qq=}}, founded by [[:en:Gyōki|Gyōki]], located in [[:en:Arima Onsen|Arima Onsen]]. It was the site of a grand tea ceremony hosted by [[:en:Toyotomi Hideyoshi|Toyotomi Hideyoshi]].
* {{ill|Onsen-ji (Toyooka)|ja|温泉寺 (豊岡市)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onsen-ji (Toyooka)|qq=}}  -  A [[:en:Kōyasan Shingon-shū|Kōyasan Shingon sect]] temple in {{ill|Toyooka, Hyōgo|ja|豊岡市, 兵庫県|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toyooka, Hyōgo|qq=}}, serving as the guardian temple of {{ill|Kinosaki Onsen|ja|城崎温泉|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kinosaki Onsen|qq=}}.

